  We use the fact that if two functions are equal, then `P` applied to them is equivalent. Specifically, `P.congr_arg h1` implies that `P (fun n => n - n)` is the same as `P (fun n => 0)`. Since the original goal is `P (fun n => n - n)`, we can use `by assumption` to close the proof.

